title: MacBook Pro 13" A1502 820-4924 liquid damage not turning on
message:
Hi,
We got a mentioned MacBook with was liquid damaged.
Liquid damage was around Q8175, Q6060, u5870
I cleaned up board and fixed broken traces around Q8175
CPU_VCCST_PWRGD present 1.02V
Rail 3,34V present
PPbus_S5_hscomputing present 11.8V
cpuvr_phase1 = 1.86v
cpuvr_phase2 = 1.86v
L7630 voltage present 1,05V
once I connect mouse to usb it blinks and thats it
no chime no display
cpu gets warm.
FAN spin for me ones.
Any ideas?

title: MacBook Pro 13" A1502 820-4924 liquid damage not turning on
message:
Fan doesn't spin untill CPU gets really hot on this model.
Mouse just flash once, no steady light?

I cannot locate Q8175 on schematic...

Try to start in SMC bypass mode.

MacBook Pro 13" A1502 820-4924 liquid damage not turning on
message: Laptop fixed, U1950 was faulty. Thanks for any help.
